description:
EthernetPort: Table containing Ethernet port attributes for various network elements.

dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the data was recorded.
Area_Name: Geographic area where the Ethernet port is located (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
CellId: Identifier for the cell or site where the Ethernet port resides.
Id2: Redundant identifier, possibly mirroring CellId.
Id3:  Secondary identifier for the Ethernet port (e.g., TN_IDL_A_2).
vsDataType: Type of data in the record (e.g., vsDataEthernetPort).
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
EthernetPort.supplicant:  Details about the 802.1x supplicant (appears empty).
EthernetPort.encapsulation:  Detailed description of the Ethernet port's encapsulation and context within the network.
EthernetPort.userLabel: User-friendly label for the Ethernet port (often matches Id3).
EthernetPort.holdDownTimer:  Timer value for hold-down mechanisms (appears empty).
EthernetPort.mtu: Maximum Transmission Unit size in bytes.
EthernetPort.egressQosClassification: QoS classification for outgoing traffic (appears empty).
EthernetPort.macAddress: MAC address of the Ethernet port.
EthernetPort.ethernetPortId: Unique identifier for the Ethernet port (often matches Id3 and userLabel).
EthernetPort.admOperatingMode: Administratively configured operating mode (e.g., 10G_FULL, 1G_FULL).
EthernetPort.egressQosMarking: QoS marking for outgoing traffic (appears empty).
EthernetPort.administrativeState: Administrative state of the Ethernet port (e.g., UNLOCKED).
EthernetPort.reservedBy: Information about what entity has reserved the Ethernet port.
EthernetPort.ingressQosMarking: QoS marking for incoming traffic (appears empty).
EthernetPort.operOperatingMode: Operationally active operating mode (e.g., 10G_FULL, 1G_FULL).
EthernetPort.egressQosQueueMap: Mapping of egress traffic to QoS queues (appears empty).
EthernetPort.lldpTransmit: LLDP transmit status (e.g., DISABLED).
EthernetPort.autoNegEnable: Status of autonegotiation (e.g., true, false).
